# Steps to install SASS

# 1. (Optional) Install Node Version Manager (nvm) to manage Node.js versions:
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

# 2. Exit the terminal and reopen it to reload the shell with nvm.

# 3. Install Node.js version 20.16 using nvm:
nvm install 20.16
nvm use 20.16

# 4. Verify node and npm installation:
node -v
npm -v

# 5. Install SASS globally (or locally) using npm:
npm install sass -v 3.7.4

# 6. Verify SASS installation:
npx sass --version
